HEADWORD: Spissated
<hw>Spis"sa*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Rendered dense or
compact, as by evaporation; inspissated; thickened.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spissated</qex> juice of the poppy.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spissitude</ent>⟦br⟧
